<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-12-15T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-12-15T16:00:00-05:00" n="233" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/107a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-12-15T16:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">December 15,
                                        1919, 4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Consult Stabler concerning his telegram December 4 to Merrill. Advise
                            Department result of your conference with Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            mentioned therein. Why is signing of decree still delayed?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>